<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-11-08T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-11-08T10:00:00-05:00" n="218" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.032/103: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-11-08T10:00:00-05:00">November 8, 1930—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>226. Department’s 127, November 7, 6 p.m.<note n="41" xml:id="d218fn41">Not printed.</note> Decree convoking legislative bodies in
                            extraordinary session on November 10th, next, has been promulgated.
                            Legislature will assemble on the 10th and organize. When organized, both
                            bodies will report to President Roy who will then call them to meet as
                            National Assembly. It will take about a week to organize, including the
                            examination of credentials.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>